File: Former president Jacob Zuma. AFP/Kim Ludbrook JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Commission is to lay contempt charges against former President Jacob Zuma in the Constitutional Court. The commission wants him jailed for two years and wants Police Minister Bheki Cele and National Police Commissioner Khehkla Sitole to make the arrest. Zuma disobeyed a summons to appear before the commission last week. WATCH: A real prospect of jail time for Jacob Zuma In November, he left the commission during a lunch break. This prompted inquiry chairperson Raymond Zondo to head to the Constitutional Court and order Zuma's return. The commission also says Zuma didn't submit affidavits regarding Prasa and Eskom, despite being ordered to do so.